{\noindent} We now consider what happens to the primary constraint found in beyond Horndeski, when we combine this theory with the Horndeski one.
We will show that, when mixing actions of different orders, generically the primary constraint of the kind (\ref{primary-BH}) is lost.
In this regard, it is enough to consider only the highest order terms in the extrinsic curvature.

${\cal B}$ and ${\cal K}$ in Horndeski theories obey the following relations
\begin{eqnarray}
